    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="about-section-2">
    <div class="section-2-info">
      <h2>Biggest caiçaras on the island</h2>
      <div class="section-2-text">
        <h5>In Tupi, caiçara means man of the Coast</h5>
        <p>Aventureiro is a fishermen village with around 100 locals, a community that has been there for over 200 years preserving their traditions and memories of love, rescues and great journeys. Their economy is based on artisanal fishing, sustainable agriculture and touristic activities.</p>
        <h5>Community Based Tourism</h5>
        <p>Different than other parts of the island, where big tourism corporations run the business, the touristic activities in Aventureiro are all managed by the caiçaras, local residents of the beach, who have special authorization to host up until 560 travelers per day on the Reserve.<strong> If you are a tourist, you need to get a permit before visiting.</strong></p>
        <h5>Culture and Activities</h5>
        <p>On the first full moon weekend of January, locals host the typical Santa Cruz procession and in July, they have Festa Junina. Besides the Santa Cruz church, Aventureiro also has one elementary school and several restaurants and bars, which are people's houses turned into social and service areas.
        Energy is powered by gasoline/diesel generators, which are usually turned on at 6pm and off at 10pm. Surfing, fishing, crafting, cooking, making music and playing football are some of the most common activities on the beach.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="about-section-3" style="background-image: url('<%= image_path "onda.svg"%>')">
    <div class="section-3-info">
      <h2>The Adventurer Guide</h2>
